# Project Conventions

- **Stack**: Expo 55, React Native, TypeScript. Use expo-router for navigation.
- **Path alias**: Import from `@/` (maps to `src/`). Example: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'`.
- **File layout**:
  - `src/app/` – expo-router screens and layouts
  - `src/components/` – shared UI (including `ui/` for Reusables)
  - `src/hooks/` – custom hooks
  - `src/lib/` – Firebase, auth, Firestore, Storage helpers
  - `src/contexts/` – React context providers (e.g. Auth)
  - `src/constants/` – theme, config constants
- **Domain**: Event-based dating platform (see core-product-concept rule). Users sign up, maintain a dating profile (bio, photos, interests), and see a dashboard when signed in; events, host flows, and post-event matching are part of the product vision.
- **Documentation**: High-level app description lives in [docs/APP.md](docs/APP.md). System-specific docs (auth, Firebase, profile flow, **progressive profile vision**, TanStack Query) live in [docs/skills/](docs/skills/). Keep these in sync when changing behavior (see docs-and-rules rule).
